The paper discusses the development of a language implementation framework and an instrumentation framework for software development tools, which suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also emphasizes the importance of performance (cs.DC) and usability (cs.SY) in tool development. Finally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG) in some of the developed tools.
